solution:
Divide the larger square into 8 congruent triangles, as shown, 4 of which make up the smaller square. [asy]
pair a=(0,1),b=(1,0),c=(0,-1),d=(-1,0);
draw((-1,-1)--(-1,1)--(1,1)--(1,-1)--cycle);
filldraw(a--b--c--d--cycle, lightred, black);
draw(d--b, linetype("8 8"));
draw(a--c, linetype("8 8"));
