problem:
For some constants $a$ and $b,$ let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
ax + b & \text{if } x < 2, \\
8 - 3x & \text{if } x \ge 2.
\end{array}
\right.\]The function $f$ has the property that $f(f(x)) = x$ for all $x.$ What is $a + b?$

solution:
We expand each product separately: \begin{align*}
(2x-5)(x+7) &= 2x(x) + 2x(7) -5(x) -5(7)\\
&=2x^2 +14x - 5x -35\\
&= 2x^2 +9x - 35
\end{align*}and \begin{align*}
(x+5)(2x-1) &=x(2x) + x(-1) +5(2x) + 5(-1)\\
&=2x^2 -x + 10x -5\\
&=2x^2 +9x - 5.
\end{align*}So, we have  \begin{align*}&\ \ \ \ (2x-5)(x+7) - (x+5)(2x-1) \\&= 2x^2+9x -35 - (2x^2 +9x -5) = \boxed{-30}.\end{align*}

