All points on the line $x=-3$ are of the form $(-3,y)$, where $y$ is a real number.  The distance from $(5,2)$ to $(-3,y)$ is $$\sqrt{(5-(-3))^2+(2-y)^2}$$ units.  Setting this expression equal to 10, we find \begin{align*}
\sqrt{(5-(-3))^2+(2-y)^2}&= 10 \\
64+(2-y)^2&= 100 \\
(2-y)^2&= 36 \\
2-y&=\pm 6 \\
y=2\pm6.
